properties.areaDesc: Mason, WA; King, WA; Snohomish, WA
properties.headline: Flood Watch issued January 1 at 4:29AM PST until January 1 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
The Flood Watch continues for

* Portions of northwest Washington and west central Washington,
including the following counties, in northwest Washington,
Mason. In west central Washington, King and Snohomish.

* Until 4 PM PST this afternoon

* Precipitation enhanced by convergence between Stevens Pass and
Snoqualmie Pass will keep the possibility of minor flooding
later today in King and Snohomish county.

* Rivers are still rising in Mason county as a result of the heavy
rain along the southern slopes of the Olympics on Tuesday. Minor
flooding is possible.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Watch means there is a potential for flooding based on
current forecasts.

You should monitor latest forecasts and be alert for possible
Flood Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be
prepared to take action should flooding develop.

NWSheadline: FLOOD WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON
